    "body": "Previously 1024 byte alignemnt was guarded only by `IsHopper`. This commit changes it to be guarded by `TargetHasBulkCopy` with the same threshold as Hopper is using.\r\n\r\nThe kernel added in the test was failing on my RTX5090 GPU.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved shared-memory alignment for GPU buffer allocation to ensure wider alignment where supported, reducing misalignment issues on modern GPU architectures.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added regression tests that verify TMA/shared-memory alignment and runtime numerical correctness across multiple GPU architectures and host CUDA testing.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
